How long has Fido been waiting
for his master?

01:47.933 --> 01:49.033
About an hour.

01:49.034 --> 01:50.301
Ever since Molly called
from Naperville

01:50.302 --> 01:51.601
when she
stopped for gas.

01:51.603 --> 01:54.237
He got so excited,
I'm surprised he hasn't piddled.

01:54.239 --> 01:56.139
(car horn honks)
What's that, boy?

01:56.141 --> 01:57.808
You hear something?

01:57.809 --> 01:58.976
Leave him alone.

01:58.977 --> 02:00.911
This is the first
time I've seen him

02:00.912 --> 02:02.680
on his hind legs
since she left.

02:02.681 --> 02:03.781
Poor thing.

02:03.782 --> 02:06.182
He's been real sad without Molly.
Mm.

02:06.184 --> 02:07.651
Celibacy will do that
to a man.

02:07.652 --> 02:09.320
That's why monks
are so quiet.

02:09.321 --> 02:11.955
If you're not getting any,
what's there to talk about?

02:13.090 --> 02:16.292
He must have been a mute
before he met Molly.

02:16.294 --> 02:17.661
Oh, there were girls.

02:17.662 --> 02:20.064
I mean, he'd lose a few pounds,
get his heart broken,

02:20.065 --> 02:24.701
then come crawling back into
the arms of his best gal.

02:24.703 --> 02:26.637
The fact that his fridge
isn't full

02:26.638 --> 02:28.572
of women's heads is a miracle.

02:28.573 --> 02:31.140
She's here! She's here!

02:34.178 --> 02:37.047
There she is!

02:37.048 --> 02:40.216
Oh, my God,
I missed you all so much!

02:40.218 --> 02:41.652
Oh, not as much
as I missed you,

02:41.653 --> 02:42.952
because I have been here
with them.

02:42.954 --> 02:44.321
All right,

02:44.322 --> 02:45.888
leave some for
the rest of us.

02:45.890 --> 02:47.590
I missed this face.

02:47.592 --> 02:48.658
Oh.

02:48.660 --> 02:50.693
It felt like
you were gone for months.

02:50.695 --> 02:52.496
Yeah, I... I actually was.

02:52.497 --> 02:54.164
Oh, come here.
Come here.

02:54.165 --> 02:55.264
VINCE:
Clear the way.

02:55.266 --> 02:56.567
Step-papa coming through. Oh!

02:56.568 --> 02:59.101
All right, all right.

02:59.103 --> 03:01.271
How great does this feel?
I ain't never letting go.

03:01.272 --> 03:02.439
All right, let go.

03:02.440 --> 03:03.774
Okay.

03:03.775 --> 03:05.141
Peggy.

03:05.143 --> 03:07.376
You look tired.

03:07.378 --> 03:10.513
It's weird, but
I actually missed that.

03:10.515 --> 03:11.715
Come on, sit down,

03:11.716 --> 03:13.583
we want to hear all about
the writing program.

03:13.584 --> 03:15.217
All right, well,
it was a doozy.

03:21.358 --> 03:23.860
Well, for eight intense weeks,
I was surrounded

03:23.861 --> 03:27.096
by brilliant novelists
and poets and playwrights.

03:27.098 --> 03:29.098
It sounds wonderful.

03:29.100 --> 03:30.500
No, it was awful.

03:30.501 --> 03:32.334
They hated my writing.

03:32.336 --> 03:34.738
Oh, honey, I'm sorry.
No, don't be.

03:34.739 --> 03:36.940
The more they hated it,
the more it drove me.

03:36.941 --> 03:38.807
I dug deep,
I found my voice.

03:38.809 --> 03:40.642
I bet you have
a beautiful voice.

03:40.644 --> 03:44.280
No. Turns out my voice
has the mouth of a sailor.

03:44.281 --> 03:45.547
Dirty?

03:45.549 --> 03:47.050
Filthy.

03:47.051 --> 03:49.919
I know I've written some racy
short stories in the past,

03:49.920 --> 03:51.587
but this new stuff
takes the cake.

03:51.589 --> 03:54.290
Actually, in the second chapter,
I wrote this thing with cake.

03:54.291 --> 03:56.091
It's disgusting.

03:56.093 --> 03:57.494
She gets it from me.

03:57.495 --> 03:59.129
You know, you never think
they're listening,

03:59.130 --> 04:01.230
but they're little sponges.

04:01.232 --> 04:05.134
You know, I mean, it started out
so innocently enough.

04:05.135 --> 04:07.303
You know, just kind of
a romantic little story

04:07.304 --> 04:09.505
about two lonely people
who meet in Chicago, and...

04:09.506 --> 04:10.872
Aw, that's us.

04:10.874 --> 04:11.773
Oh, God, no.

04:11.775 --> 04:13.076
No?
No!

04:13.077 --> 04:15.144
No, we are nothing
like these animals.

04:15.145 --> 04:16.579
No morals, no boundaries.

04:16.579 --> 04:19.148
Just two people who are
willing to stop at nothing

04:19.149 --> 04:21.315
until they satisfy
their carnal desires.

04:21.317 --> 04:23.051
Ooh, that's a spicy blurb.

04:23.053 --> 04:25.388
Well, you know what?
That's what the publisher said

04:25.389 --> 04:27.589
when he bought my book!

04:27.591 --> 04:30.192
(cheering)

04:30.194 --> 04:32.128
(indistinct, excited chatter)

04:32.129 --> 04:34.564
The school... the school
sent out samples,

04:34.565 --> 04:36.766
and out of the piles
of pretentious fire,

04:36.767 --> 04:39.201
my hot, throbbing
phoenix rose!

04:39.202 --> 04:42.538
You sold a book!
I sold a book!

04:42.539 --> 04:44.105
Son of a bitch!

